:"Create a test PR in a test GitHub organization with a multi-hunk diff (changes at lines 10 and 50 in the original file). Post inline comments at each changed location. Verify comments appear at the correct diff-relative line numbers in the PR review view, not absolute file lines.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"The test requires Integration level to accurately verify line-number mapping against GitHub's API behavior. A Unit mock without full GitHub context could miss off-by-one errors or hunk-boundary issues.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent identifies at least one real defect in a pull request that contains a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The failure is in LLM capability: the model fails to identify a bug (e.g., unchecked null dereference, SQL injection, missing error handling). A mocked LLM that returns `findings=['bug found']` passes the test but doesn't verify that a *real* LLM identifies the actual bug in a real code snippet. This is non-deterministic model behavior that cannot be tested without calling the real LLM. Different model versions, prompts, or even the same model on repeated runs may vary.","test_description":"Create a PR containing a real, introduced defect (e.g., a null pointer dereference, unchecked exception, or SQL injection vulnerability). Call the real LLM-powered review agent on this PR. Verify the agent identifies at least one finding that correctly describes the introduced bug.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"This test must use real LLM because mocked responses cannot verify defect detection capability. The behavior explicitly requires 'real defect' detection, which is an LLM capability boundary.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.9,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every finding listed in the top-level summary c